Total food produced by this province, which contributes to the factionwide food supply. If this province consumes more food than it produces, and the factionwide food supply is negative, then this province will suffer a famine.

Total gold produced by this province, after the tax bonus and corruption penalty have been applied.
This is a modifier to the income listed above. It is affected by tax level, technologies, governors, local generals, buildings, and special events or missions.
The larger your empire grows, the more corruption you will encounter. Governors can reduce corruption when assigned to a province.
Production and consumption of food and gold within this province.
The public order in this province and the factors affecting it are listed here. Negative public order incurs the risk of rebellion. The more negative public order becomes, the higher the risk.
